Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Minister of State, Dr. Ramatu Aliyu, on Saturday donated delivery kits and newborn items to 600 mothers in selected Primary Health Care Centers across the six Area Councils of the territory. It was as part of activities to celebrate the New Year. She offset the medical bills of an indigent father, Mr. Salihu Abubakar, whose wife gave birth to a triplet at the Gwagwalada Teaching Hospital. She donated cash to mothers. The minister was represented by the Special Assistant on Primary Health Care, Mr. Muhammed Ibrahim.   Wike bans nightclubs, prostitution, declares war on oil…     Ikpeazu signs 2022 budget of N147.2b into law     ‘Agric ministry spent N3.8b on Ruga scheme without…   - Advertisement - “Remember to take care of yourselves and attend post-natal clinics and continue to take your routine medicines. “On my part, I will continue to identify with you and share in your joy. “Since I came to office in 2019, I have continued to implement and support initiatives that would improve the health of mothers and children particularly towards reducing maternal and child deaths from preventable causes, also empowering women to contribute meaningfully to the upkeep of themselves and their families. “I will also encourage you to always contribute to the growth of the family in particular and the community at large. “All babies born today are welcome and I pray to God to continue to grant mothers and babies good health, while the fathers continue to have the means to support their families,” Aliyu said.